ALL Lincoln Park Families: Today (8/19) is the last day to change learning choices until December. After today, changes cannot be made to learning choices. If you want to change please call the school office, send us a Facebook message, or email us at info@acalincolnp.com

Online/Hybrid Families:
Virtual learning materials can be picked up from the school during the times listed below. Your child CANNOT start the school year without these materials. The legal guardian MUST come pick up the materials.
Lower campus has a tent in the parking lot. Upper campus is distributing from the gym doors.
Wednesday 8/19: 10-3
Thursday 8/20: 10-7
Friday 8/21: 10-3

shared_text:
Ohio State Parks is at John Bryan State Park.
June 12 at 7:22 AM ¬∑ Yellow Springs, OH ¬∑

Looking for something to do this weekend? Have you heard about our new Storybook üìö Trails? We recently opened trails at Dillon, John Bryan, Maumee Bay and Wingfoot in addition to the one we opened last year at Alum Creek. We partnered with the Ohio Governor's Imagination Library and Dolly Parton's Imagination Library to provide story content for these trails and raise awareness of these valuable resources for Ohio families. This is a wonderful way to enjoy learning while in the great outdoors! For more info, check out https://ohiodnr.gov/wps/portal/gov/odnr-core/home/news-and-events/all-news/storybook-trails-openings. Ohio Department of Education
